 ---------------- Linux Commands - Introductions ----------------------------
 
 	Basic Syntax : command -options arguments
 	
 		Multiple Options the -(option1option2...) 
 		
 		Ex. ls -alt ( OR ls -a -t -l ) 
 
 	1. pwd - Print Working Directory
 	
 	2. ls  - List The Contents of Directory
 	
 	   Shows the only visible content.
 	   
		-a  --all 		to display All directories and hidden files too . 
 	  
		-l 	 			display in long format
 		
 		-t    		 	sort  by  modification  time,  newest first

 		-r, --reverse 	everse order while sorting

        -R, --recursive list subdirectories recursively

 		-1     			list one file per line.
 		
 		Two Ways :
 				
 				a) ls 			: list all content of cwd ( Alphabetical Order )
 				
 				b) ls path1  path2  path3 ... pathn  : list all contents from all paths
 				
						ex. ls ~ ./doc	     : Display content from home and doc 	
 				
 
	3. cd - Change Working Directory
	
		Two Ways :
			
			a) Aboslute Path :	'/path' - pathname begins with root directory till the 
										  destination location/directory 
			b) Relative Path :  
					
					Two Ways :
						
						a) './'  - w.r.t cwd
						b) '../' - w.r.t parent directory of cwd
			
			cd Shortcuts :
				
				cd 		 : changes to home directory
				cd ~	 : changes to home directory
				cd -	 : changes to previously working directory
	
	4. file filename - Gives Short Description Of File and its extension
				
	5. less filename - displays Content of file in text format 				
	
	
	
